05/06/2009
LUXEMBOURG, Luxembourg -- European Commission (EC) Vice-President Jacques Barrot briefed EU interior ministers Thursday (June 4th) on the progress Western Balkan countries have made in their visa-liberalisation processes. He said that Macedonia, Montenegro and Serbia have made significant efforts to fulfil the necessary criteria for visa-free travel. Slovenian Interior Minister Katarina Kresal predicted that within weeks, the EC will propose abolishing visas for some countries, though she did not specify which. (RTCG, STA, Tanjug, Makfax - 04/06/09)
